tasks.description:
Both ActivityFeed (90 lines) and CommentSection (280 lines) render lists without virtualization. react-window is already installed (`^2.2.7`). The existing virtualization pattern is established in BacklogView.tsx / SprintSection.tsx / TableView.tsx — follow it exactly:

```tsx
const ROW_HEIGHT = 52;
const MAX_LIST_HEIGHT = 600;
const VIRTUALIZE_THRESHOLD = 20;

{items.length > VIRTUALIZE_THRESHOLD ? (
  <List
    style={{ height: Math.min(items.length * ROW_HEIGHT, MAX_LIST_HEIGHT) }}
    rowCount={items.length}
    rowHeight={ROW_HEIGHT}
    rowComponent={({ index, style }) => (
      <div style={style}>...</div>
    )}
  />
) : (
  items.map(...) // plain render for small lists
)}
```

**ActivityFeed.tsx:** Each ActivityItem is compact (~40px). Use `ROW_HEIGHT=40`, `VIRTUALIZE_THRESHOLD=50` (activities accumulate fast). Import `List` from `react-window`. Keep the existing `memo` on ActivityItem. Wrap in conditional: virtualize when `activities.length > 50`, plain map otherwise.

**CommentSection.tsx:** Comments are variable-height due to markdown content and nested replies. Two approaches — pick the simpler one: either (a) use a fixed `ROW_HEIGHT=80` for top-level comments only (replies render inside the parent row, not virtualized), or (b) add a simple 'Show more' button when `comments.length > 30` that loads the rest (simpler than variable-size virtualization). Option (b) is preferred if variable heights make react-window awkward. The key point: avoid rendering 100+ comment DOM nodes at once.

Add dark mode classes to both components while you're in there — follow the existing pattern: `bg-white dark:bg-slate-900`, `text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300`, `border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700`.
